Helm Upgrade
What is helm upgrade?

After an application is already installed in Kubernetes, you don't install it again.

Instead, you upgrade the existing release.

Syntax

	helm upgrade <RELEASE_NAME> <CHART_PATH>

Example: 

Suppose your cluster has:

Deployment
Replica: 3
Image: nginx:1.29

Now you change:

values.yaml

tag: "1.30"

Run:

helm upgrade my-release .



Helm performs these steps:

	Read Chart.yaml
        	│
	Read values.yaml
        	│
	Render templates
        	│
	Compare old manifest
        	│
	Compare new manifest
        	│
	Find differences
        	│
	Update only changed resources

Helm does not delete everything and recreate it. It updates only what changed.




Verify the Upgrade

Check releases:

	helm list

Check revision history:

	helm history my-release

You'll see something like:

REVISION    STATUS      DESCRIPTION
1           deployed    Install complete
2           deployed    Upgrade complete
3           deployed    Upgrade complete

Each successful helm upgrade creates a new revision
